name: Being with Nature
description:
I runaway, so far away from home.
Try to find out my own space.
It’s been six years, not a short of time.
A journey to find out peace.

I go there and here,
Feel like I trap in a big labyrinth.
My own labyrinth who stays in my mind.
Where’s my home?

I’m lost.
There’s no home.
I’m totally lost.
There’s no peace.

Suddenly, 
My feet walk by itself.
While my hand wipes my tears.

I go with it.
No doubt, no hesitation.
Then, I arrive, in a safe place.
It called nature.

Now I realize.
My home, my peace,
is not going anywhere.
It’s here, on nature.
